commit.message: Update version to 2.5
Update version of six required

Ensure binary text written to fd

To provide Python 2 / 3 compatibility, we need to ensure text written to
the tracker file is binary since the fd is always opened in binary mode.

Ensure unicode content string from http.request (#46)

For Python 2 / 3 compatibility, we need to ensure that the content
string returned from httplib2.Http().request is Unicode. json.loads in
Python 3 only handles Unicode strings, necessitating this change.

commit.message: Update version to v2.4

Improve handling PKCS 12 keys (#45)

When attempting to load a PKCS 12 key in Python 3, io.open would
throw an error since it tried to apply UTF-8 text encoding to the
key file, which was not a compatible text file

commit.message: Use io.open for compatibility
Update version to 2.2
Updates auth endpoints. Fixes #42.
cgi.parse_qs is deprecated, using urllib.parse.parse_qs instead
Update version to 2.1.

Add RAPT caching & scopes for narrowing challenges in reauth flows.

- Cache RAPT to prevent frequent reauth challenges.

- This plugin is mainly used by gsutil, or with refresh tokens obtained
through gsutil (see instructions at [1]), and thus we expect refresh
tokens to usually have the cloud-platform API scope. We set this in
the default RAPT scopes, but we define the defaults at module level so
they may be easily overridden for use in other contexts as necessary.

Context from issue tracker:
https://issuetracker.google.com/issues/35099526#comment52

[1] https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/boto-plugin
Update version to 2.0
Add Python 3 support, move from mox->mock.
Fix requirements in req file and setup.py.
Add reauth credential support.
Fix linter warnings & Py2-only syntax for excepts
